Class Long2ReferenceAVLTreeMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<Long,​V>, Long2ReferenceFunction<V>, Long2ReferenceMap<V>, Long2ReferenceSortedMap<V>, Serializable, Cloneable, Function<Long,​V>, LongFunction<V>, Map<Long,​V>, SortedMap<Long,​V>
    public class Long2ReferenceAVLTreeMap<V>
extends AbstractLong2ReferenceSortedMap<V>
implements Serializable, Cloneable
    A type-specific AVL tree map with a fast, small-footprint implementation.

    The iterators provided by the views of this class are type-specific bidirectional iterators. Moreover, the iterator returned by iterator() can be safely cast to a type-specific list iterator.

      • clone

        public Long2ReferenceAVLTreeMap<V> clone()
        Returns a deep copy of this tree map.
